<title>JAPAN: Japan offers 500 bln yen in 1.8 pct six-year bonds.</title>
<headline>Japan offers 500 bln yen in 1.8 pct six-year bonds.</headline>
<dateline>TOKYO 1997-05-08</dateline>
<text>
<p>The Ministry of Finance said on Thursday it would offer 500 billion yen worth of 1.8 percent six-year bonds through a price competitive auction.</p>
<p>The auction will close at noon 0300 GMT and the results will be announced at 2.30 p.m. 0530 GMT.</p>
<p>The issue date will be May 20 and maturity date May 20, 2003.</p>
